# Novopetrovka, Sharansky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Novopetrovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Michurinsky Selsoviet, Sharansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 40 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Novopetrovka is located 33 km northeast of Sharan (the district's administrative centre) by road. Borisovka is the nearest rural locality.
